article.headline: Eastern Michigan 71, Northern Colorado 61
article.story: YPSILANTI, Mich. (AP) -- Carlos Medlock had 20 points and Jesse Bunkley scored all 19 of his points in the second half Thursday to lift Eastern Michigan to a 71-61 victory over Northern Colorado. Freshman Devon Dumes also had 10 points for the Eagles (2-7), who snapped a six-game losing streak. Sean Taibi and Kirk Archibeque had 14 and 12 points, respectively, for the Bears (2-10). Northern Colorado has lost five of its last six games. Northern Colorado scored 10 of the first 12 points of the second half to go ahead 40-36. After Eastern Michigan evened the game at 42, Bunkley hit three straight 3-pointers to put the Eagles up 51-42 with 11:34 left. Eastern Michigan built its cushion to as much as 12 points and did not let Northern Colorado any closer than seven points the rest of the game. There were three ties and three lead changes during the first half. Despite having several scoreless periods during the half, Eastern Michigan was able to build a seven-point lead and held on for a 34-30 halftime advantage.
